2. Parashuram Economic Development Corporation to receive Rs. 28 lakh (Rupees Twenty-eight Lakhs only) as follows:
The Government is approving the distribution subject to the following terms and conditions:
1) To streamline operations with a view to limiting expenditure on management.
2) Detailed information about the amounts spent on various matters and the expenditure incurred on them.
The information should be submitted to the government.
3) Cut down on office expenses.
4) Submission of utility certificate to the Government and concerned from time to time after such expenditure.
The responsibility will rest with the Managing Director, Parashuram Economic Development Corporation, Pune.
5) The actual expenditure incurred for the purpose and recorded by the Office of the Principal Accountant General, Mumbai.
The corporation should take action to adjust the cost.
6) The funds are not spent under any circumstances, be it in a bank account, a personal account, or a government account.
Cannot be left out of the text.
7) Such non-spending funds if the funds are withdrawn and kept in a bank / personal bank account.
Government accounts should be deposited.
